4888bool
4889ARMBaseInstrInfo::isFpMLxInstruction(unsigned Opcode, unsigned &MulOpc,
4890 unsigned &AddSubOpc,
4891 bool &NegAcc, bool &HasLane) const {
4892 DenseMap<unsigned, unsigned>::const_iterator I = MLxEntryMap.find(Opcode);
4893 if (I == MLxEntryMap.end())
4894 return false;
4895
4896 const ARM_MLxEntry &Entry = ARM_MLxTable[I->second];
4897 MulOpc = Entry.MulOpc;
4898 AddSubOpc = Entry.AddSubOpc;
4899 NegAcc = Entry.NegAcc;
4900 HasLane = Entry.HasLane;
4901 return true;
4902}
4903
4904//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4905// Execution domains.
4906//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4907//
4908// Some instructions go down the NEON pipeline, some go down the VFP pipeline,
4909// and some can go down both. The vmov instructions go down the VFP pipeline,
4910// but they can be changed to vorr equivalents that are executed by the NEON
4911// pipeline.
4912//
4913// We use the following execution domain numbering:
4914//
4915enum ARMExeDomain {
4916 ExeGeneric = 0,
4917 ExeVFP = 1,
4918 ExeNEON = 2
4919};
4920
4921//
4922// Also see ARMInstrFormats.td and Domain* enums in ARMBaseInfo.h
4923//
4924std::pair<uint16_t, uint16_t>
4925ARMBaseInstrInfo::getExecutionDomain(const MachineInstr &MI) const {
4926 // If we don't have access to NEON instructions then we won't be able
4927 // to swizzle anything to the NEON domain. Check to make sure.
4928 if (Subtarget.hasNEON()) {
4929 // VMOVD, VMOVRS and VMOVSR are VFP instructions, but can be changed to NEON
4930 // if they are not predicated.
4931 if (MI.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVD && !isPredicated(MI))
4932 return std::make_pair(ExeVFP, (1 << ExeVFP) | (1 << ExeNEON));
4933
4934 // CortexA9 is particularly picky about mixing the two and wants these
4935 // converted.
4936 if (Subtarget.useNEONForFPMovs() && !isPredicated(MI) &&
4937 (MI.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVRS || MI.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVSR ||
4938 MI.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVS))
4939 return std::make_pair(ExeVFP, (1 << ExeVFP) | (1 << ExeNEON));
4940 }
4941 // No other instructions can be swizzled, so just determine their domain.
4942 unsigned Domain = MI.getDesc().TSFlags & ARMII::DomainMask;
4943
4944 if (Domain & ARMII::DomainNEON)
4945 return std::make_pair(ExeNEON, 0);
4946
4947 // Certain instructions can go either way on Cortex-A8.
4948 // Treat them as NEON instructions.
4949 if ((Domain & ARMII::DomainNEONA8) && Subtarget.isCortexA8())
4950 return std::make_pair(ExeNEON, 0);
4951
4952 if (Domain & ARMII::DomainVFP)
4953 return std::make_pair(ExeVFP, 0);
4954
4955 return std::make_pair(ExeGeneric, 0);
4956}
4957
4958static unsigned getCorrespondingDRegAndLane(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
4959 unsigned SReg, unsigned &Lane) {
4960 unsigned DReg = TRI->getMatchingSuperReg(SReg, ARM::ssub_0, &ARM::DPRRegClass);
4961 Lane = 0;
4962
4963 if (DReg != ARM::NoRegister)
4964 return DReg;
4965
4966 Lane = 1;
4967 DReg = TRI->getMatchingSuperReg(SReg, ARM::ssub_1, &ARM::DPRRegClass);
4968
4969 assert(DReg && "S-register with no D super-register?");
4970 return DReg;
4971}
4972
4973/// getImplicitSPRUseForDPRUse - Given a use of a DPR register and lane,
4974/// set ImplicitSReg to a register number that must be marked as implicit-use or
4975/// zero if no register needs to be defined as implicit-use.
4976///
4977/// If the function cannot determine if an SPR should be marked implicit use or
4978/// not, it returns false.
4979///
4980/// This function handles cases where an instruction is being modified from taking
4981/// an SPR to a DPR[Lane]. A use of the DPR is being added, which may conflict
4982/// with an earlier def of an SPR corresponding to DPR[Lane^1] (i.e. the other
4983/// lane of the DPR).
4984///
4985/// If the other SPR is defined, an implicit-use of it should be added. Else,
4986/// (including the case where the DPR itself is defined), it should not.
4987///
4988static bool getImplicitSPRUseForDPRUse(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
4989 MachineInstr &MI, unsigned DReg,
4990 unsigned Lane, unsigned &ImplicitSReg) {
4991 // If the DPR is defined or used already, the other SPR lane will be chained
4992 // correctly, so there is nothing to be done.
4993 if (MI.definesRegister(DReg, TRI) || MI.readsRegister(DReg, TRI)) {
4994 ImplicitSReg = 0;
4995 return true;
4996 }
4997
4998 // Otherwise we need to go searching to see if the SPR is set explicitly.
4999 ImplicitSReg = TRI->getSubReg(DReg,
5000 (Lane & 1) ? ARM::ssub_0 : ARM::ssub_1);
5001 MachineBasicBlock::LivenessQueryResult LQR =
5002 MI.getParent()->computeRegisterLiveness(TRI, ImplicitSReg, MI);
5003
5004 if (LQR == MachineBasicBlock::LQR_Live)
5005 return true;
5006 else if (LQR == MachineBasicBlock::LQR_Unknown)
5007 return false;
5008
5009 // If the register is known not to be live, there is no need to add an
5010 // implicit-use.
5011 ImplicitSReg = 0;
5012 return true;
5013}
5014
5015void ARMBaseInstrInfo::setExecutionDomain(MachineInstr &MI,
5016 unsigned Domain) const {
5017 unsigned DstReg, SrcReg, DReg;
5018 unsigned Lane;
5019 MachineInstrBuilder MIB(*MI.getParent()->getParent(), MI);
5020 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = &getRegisterInfo();
5021 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
5022 default:
5023 llvm_unreachable("cannot handle opcode!");
5024 break;
5025 case ARM::VMOVD:
5026 if (Domain != ExeNEON)
5027 break;
5028
5029 // Zap the predicate operands.
5030 assert(!isPredicated(MI) && "Cannot predicate a VORRd");
5031
5032 // Make sure we've got NEON instructions.
5033 assert(Subtarget.hasNEON() && "VORRd requires NEON");
5034
5035 // Source instruction is %DDst = VMOVD %DSrc, 14, %noreg (; implicits)
5036 DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
5037 SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5038
5039 for (unsigned i = MI.getDesc().getNumOperands(); i; --i)
5040 MI.RemoveOperand(i - 1);
5041
5042 // Change to a %DDst = VORRd %DSrc, %DSrc, 14, %noreg (; implicits)
5043 MI.setDesc(get(ARM::VORRd));
5044 MIB.addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define)
5045 .addReg(SrcReg)
5046 .addReg(SrcReg)
5047 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
5048 break;
5049 case ARM::VMOVRS:
5050 if (Domain != ExeNEON)
5051 break;
5052 assert(!isPredicated(MI) && "Cannot predicate a VGETLN");
5053
5054 // Source instruction is %RDst = VMOVRS %SSrc, 14, %noreg (; implicits)
5055 DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
5056 SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5057
5058 for (unsigned i = MI.getDesc().getNumOperands(); i; --i)
5059 MI.RemoveOperand(i - 1);
5060
5061 DReg = getCorrespondingDRegAndLane(TRI, SrcReg, Lane);
5062
5063 // Convert to %RDst = VGETLNi32 %DSrc, Lane, 14, %noreg (; imps)
5064 // Note that DSrc has been widened and the other lane may be undef, which
5065 // contaminates the entire register.
5066 MI.setDesc(get(ARM::VGETLNi32));
5067 MIB.addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define)
5068 .addReg(DReg, RegState::Undef)
5069 .addImm(Lane)
5070 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
5071
5072 // The old source should be an implicit use, otherwise we might think it
5073 // was dead before here.
5074 MIB.addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Implicit);
5075 break;
5076 case ARM::VMOVSR: {
5077 if (Domain != ExeNEON)
5078 break;
5079 assert(!isPredicated(MI) && "Cannot predicate a VSETLN");
5080
5081 // Source instruction is %SDst = VMOVSR %RSrc, 14, %noreg (; implicits)
5082 DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
5083 SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5084
5085 DReg = getCorrespondingDRegAndLane(TRI, DstReg, Lane);
5086
5087 unsigned ImplicitSReg;
5088 if (!getImplicitSPRUseForDPRUse(TRI, MI, DReg, Lane, ImplicitSReg))
5089 break;
5090
5091 for (unsigned i = MI.getDesc().getNumOperands(); i; --i)
5092 MI.RemoveOperand(i - 1);
5093
5094 // Convert to %DDst = VSETLNi32 %DDst, %RSrc, Lane, 14, %noreg (; imps)
5095 // Again DDst may be undefined at the beginning of this instruction.
5096 MI.setDesc(get(ARM::VSETLNi32));
5097 MIB.addReg(DReg, RegState::Define)
5098 .addReg(DReg, getUndefRegState(!MI.readsRegister(DReg, TRI)))
5099 .addReg(SrcReg)
5100 .addImm(Lane)
5101 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
5102
5103 // The narrower destination must be marked as set to keep previous chains
5104 // in place.
5105 MIB.addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | RegState::Implicit);
5106 if (ImplicitSReg != 0)
5107 MIB.addReg(ImplicitSReg, RegState::Implicit);
5108 break;
5109 }
5110 case ARM::VMOVS: {
5111 if (Domain != ExeNEON)
5112 break;
5113
5114 // Source instruction is %SDst = VMOVS %SSrc, 14, %noreg (; implicits)
5115 DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
5116 SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5117
5118 unsigned DstLane = 0, SrcLane = 0, DDst, DSrc;
5119 DDst = getCorrespondingDRegAndLane(TRI, DstReg, DstLane);
5120 DSrc = getCorrespondingDRegAndLane(TRI, SrcReg, SrcLane);
5121
5122 unsigned ImplicitSReg;
5123 if (!getImplicitSPRUseForDPRUse(TRI, MI, DSrc, SrcLane, ImplicitSReg))
5124 break;
5125
5126 for (unsigned i = MI.getDesc().getNumOperands(); i; --i)
5127 MI.RemoveOperand(i - 1);
5128
5129 if (DSrc == DDst) {
5130 // Destination can be:
5131 // %DDst = VDUPLN32d %DDst, Lane, 14, %noreg (; implicits)
5132 MI.setDesc(get(ARM::VDUPLN32d));
5133 MIB.addReg(DDst, RegState::Define)
5134 .addReg(DDst, getUndefRegState(!MI.readsRegister(DDst, TRI)))
5135 .addImm(SrcLane)
5136 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
5137
5138 // Neither the source or the destination are naturally represented any
5139 // more, so add them in manually.
5140 MIB.addReg(DstReg, RegState::Implicit | RegState::Define);
5141 MIB.addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Implicit);
5142 if (ImplicitSReg != 0)
5143 MIB.addReg(ImplicitSReg, RegState::Implicit);
5144 break;
5145 }
5146
5147 // In general there's no single instruction that can perform an S <-> S
5148 // move in NEON space, but a pair of VEXT instructions *can* do the
5149 // job. It turns out that the VEXTs needed will only use DSrc once, with
5150 // the position based purely on the combination of lane-0 and lane-1
5151 // involved. For example
5152 // vmov s0, s2 -> vext.32 d0, d0, d1, #1 vext.32 d0, d0, d0, #1
5153 // vmov s1, s3 -> vext.32 d0, d1, d0, #1 vext.32 d0, d0, d0, #1
5154 // vmov s0, s3 -> vext.32 d0, d0, d0, #1 vext.32 d0, d1, d0, #1
5155 // vmov s1, s2 -> vext.32 d0, d0, d0, #1 vext.32 d0, d0, d1, #1
5156 //
5157 // Pattern of the MachineInstrs is:
5158 // %DDst = VEXTd32 %DSrc1, %DSrc2, Lane, 14, %noreg (;implicits)
5159 MachineInstrBuilder NewMIB;
5160 NewMIB = BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(ARM::VEXTd32),
5161 DDst);
5162
5163 // On the first instruction, both DSrc and DDst may be undef if present.
5164 // Specifically when the original instruction didn't have them as an
5165 // <imp-use>.
5166 unsigned CurReg = SrcLane == 1 && DstLane == 1 ? DSrc : DDst;
5167 bool CurUndef = !MI.readsRegister(CurReg, TRI);
5168 NewMIB.addReg(CurReg, getUndefRegState(CurUndef));
5169
5170 CurReg = SrcLane == 0 && DstLane == 0 ? DSrc : DDst;
5171 CurUndef = !MI.readsRegister(CurReg, TRI);
5172 NewMIB.addReg(CurReg, getUndefRegState(CurUndef))
5173 .addImm(1)
5174 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
5175
5176 if (SrcLane == DstLane)
5177 NewMIB.addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Implicit);
5178
5179 MI.setDesc(get(ARM::VEXTd32));
5180 MIB.addReg(DDst, RegState::Define);
5181
5182 // On the second instruction, DDst has definitely been defined above, so
5183 // it is not undef. DSrc, if present, can be undef as above.
5184 CurReg = SrcLane == 1 && DstLane == 0 ? DSrc : DDst;
5185 CurUndef = CurReg == DSrc && !MI.readsRegister(CurReg, TRI);
5186 MIB.addReg(CurReg, getUndefRegState(CurUndef));
5187
5188 CurReg = SrcLane == 0 && DstLane == 1 ? DSrc : DDst;
5189 CurUndef = CurReg == DSrc && !MI.readsRegister(CurReg, TRI);
5190 MIB.addReg(CurReg, getUndefRegState(CurUndef))
5191 .addImm(1)
5192 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
5193
5194 if (SrcLane != DstLane)
5195 MIB.addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Implicit);
5196
5197 // As before, the original destination is no longer represented, add it
5198 // implicitly.
5199 MIB.addReg(DstReg, RegState::Define | RegState::Implicit);
5200 if (ImplicitSReg != 0)
5201 MIB.addReg(ImplicitSReg, RegState::Implicit);
5202 break;
5203 }
5204 }
5205}
5206
5207//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5208// Partial register updates
5209//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5210//
5211// Swift renames NEON registers with 64-bit granularity. That means any
5212// instruction writing an S-reg implicitly reads the containing D-reg. The
5213// problem is mostly avoided by translating f32 operations to v2f32 operations
5214// on D-registers, but f32 loads are still a problem.
5215//
5216// These instructions can load an f32 into a NEON register:
5217//
5218// VLDRS - Only writes S, partial D update.
5219// VLD1LNd32 - Writes all D-regs, explicit partial D update, 2 uops.
5220// VLD1DUPd32 - Writes all D-regs, no partial reg update, 2 uops.
5221//
5222// FCONSTD can be used as a dependency-breaking instruction.
5223unsigned ARMBaseInstrInfo::getPartialRegUpdateClearance(
5224 const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpNum,
5225 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) const {
5226 auto PartialUpdateClearance = Subtarget.getPartialUpdateClearance();
5227 if (!PartialUpdateClearance)
5228 return 0;
5229
5230 assert(TRI && "Need TRI instance");
5231
5232 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpNum);
5233 if (MO.readsReg())
5234 return 0;
5235 Register Reg = MO.getReg();
5236 int UseOp = -1;
5237
5238 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
5239 // Normal instructions writing only an S-register.
5240 case ARM::VLDRS:
5241 case ARM::FCONSTS:
5242 case ARM::VMOVSR:
5243 case ARM::VMOVv8i8:
5244 case ARM::VMOVv4i16:
5245 case ARM::VMOVv2i32:
5246 case ARM::VMOVv2f32:
5247 case ARM::VMOVv1i64:
5248 UseOp = MI.findRegisterUseOperandIdx(Reg, false, TRI);
5249 break;
5250
5251 // Explicitly reads the dependency.
5252 case ARM::VLD1LNd32:
5253 UseOp = 3;
5254 break;
5255 default:
5256 return 0;
5257 }
5258
5259 // If this instruction actually reads a value from Reg, there is no unwanted
5260 // dependency.
5261 if (UseOp != -1 && MI.getOperand(UseOp).readsReg())
5262 return 0;
5263
5264 // We must be able to clobber the whole D-reg.
5265 if (Register::isVirtualRegister(Reg)) {
5266 // Virtual register must be a def undef foo:ssub_0 operand.
5267 if (!MO.getSubReg() || MI.readsVirtualRegister(Reg))
5268 return 0;
5269 } else if (ARM::SPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) {
5270 // Physical register: MI must define the full D-reg.
5271 unsigned DReg = TRI->getMatchingSuperReg(Reg, ARM::ssub_0,
5272 &ARM::DPRRegClass);
5273 if (!DReg || !MI.definesRegister(DReg, TRI))
5274 return 0;
5275 }
5276
5277 // MI has an unwanted D-register dependency.
5278 // Avoid defs in the previous N instructrions.
5279 return PartialUpdateClearance;
5280}
5281
5282// Break a partial register dependency after getPartialRegUpdateClearance
5283// returned non-zero.
5284void ARMBaseInstrInfo::breakPartialRegDependency(
5285 MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpNum, const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) const {
5286 assert(OpNum < MI.getDesc().getNumDefs() && "OpNum is not a def");
5287 assert(TRI && "Need TRI instance");
5288
5289 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpNum);
5290 Register Reg = MO.getReg();
5291 assert(Register::isPhysicalRegister(Reg) &&
5292 "Can't break virtual register dependencies.");
5293 unsigned DReg = Reg;
5294
5295 // If MI defines an S-reg, find the corresponding D super-register.
5296 if (ARM::SPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) {
5297 DReg = ARM::D0 + (Reg - ARM::S0) / 2;
5298 assert(TRI->isSuperRegister(Reg, DReg) && "Register enums broken");
5299 }
5300
5301 assert(ARM::DPRRegClass.contains(DReg) && "Can only break D-reg deps");
5302 assert(MI.definesRegister(DReg, TRI) && "MI doesn't clobber full D-reg");
5303
5304 // FIXME: In some cases, VLDRS can be changed to a VLD1DUPd32 which defines
5305 // the full D-register by loading the same value to both lanes. The
5306 // instruction is micro-coded with 2 uops, so don't do this until we can
5307 // properly schedule micro-coded instructions. The dispatcher stalls cause
5308 // too big regressions.
5309
5310 // Insert the dependency-breaking FCONSTD before MI.
5311 // 96 is the encoding of 0.5, but the actual value doesn't matter here.
5312 BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(ARM::FCONSTD), DReg)
5313 .addImm(96)
5314 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
5315 MI.addRegisterKilled(DReg, TRI, true);
5316}

5319 return Subtarget.getFeatureBits()[ARM::HasV6KOps];
5320}
5321
5322bool ARMBaseInstrInfo::isSwiftFastImmShift(const MachineInstr *MI) const {
5323 if (MI->getNumOperands() < 4)
5324 return true;
5325 unsigned ShOpVal = MI->getOperand(3).getImm();
5326 unsigned ShImm = ARM_AM::getSORegOffset(ShOpVal);
5327 // Swift supports faster shifts for: lsl 2, lsl 1, and lsr 1.
5328 if ((ShImm == 1 && ARM_AM::getSORegShOp(ShOpVal) == ARM_AM::lsr) ||
5329 ((ShImm == 1 || ShImm == 2) &&
5330 ARM_AM::getSORegShOp(ShOpVal) == ARM_AM::lsl))
5331 return true;
5332
5333 return false;
5334}
5335
5336bool ARMBaseInstrInfo::getRegSequenceLikeInputs(
5337 const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned DefIdx,
5338 SmallVectorImpl<RegSubRegPairAndIdx> &InputRegs) const {
5339 assert(DefIdx < MI.getDesc().getNumDefs() && "Invalid definition index");
5340 assert(MI.isRegSequenceLike() && "Invalid kind of instruction");
5341
5342 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
5343 case ARM::VMOVDRR:
5344 // dX = VMOVDRR rY, rZ
5345 // is the same as:
5346 // dX = REG_SEQUENCE rY, ssub_0, rZ, ssub_1
5347 // Populate the InputRegs accordingly.
5348 // rY
5349 const MachineOperand *MOReg = &MI.getOperand(1);
5350 if (!MOReg->isUndef())
5351 InputRegs.push_back(RegSubRegPairAndIdx(MOReg->getReg(),
5352 MOReg->getSubReg(), ARM::ssub_0));
5353 // rZ
5354 MOReg = &MI.getOperand(2);
5355 if (!MOReg->isUndef())
5356 InputRegs.push_back(RegSubRegPairAndIdx(MOReg->getReg(),
5357 MOReg->getSubReg(), ARM::ssub_1));
5358 return true;
5359 }
5360 llvm_unreachable("Target dependent opcode missing");
5361}
5362
5363bool ARMBaseInstrInfo::getExtractSubregLikeInputs(
5364 const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned DefIdx,
5365 RegSubRegPairAndIdx &InputReg) const {
5366 assert(DefIdx < MI.getDesc().getNumDefs() && "Invalid definition index");
5367 assert(MI.isExtractSubregLike() && "Invalid kind of instruction");
5368
5369 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
5370 case ARM::VMOVRRD:
5371 // rX, rY = VMOVRRD dZ
5372 // is the same as:
5373 // rX = EXTRACT_SUBREG dZ, ssub_0
5374 // rY = EXTRACT_SUBREG dZ, ssub_1
5375 const MachineOperand &MOReg = MI.getOperand(2);
5376 if (MOReg.isUndef())
5377 return false;
5378 InputReg.Reg = MOReg.getReg();
5379 InputReg.SubReg = MOReg.getSubReg();
5380 InputReg.SubIdx = DefIdx == 0 ? ARM::ssub_0 : ARM::ssub_1;
5381 return true;
5382 }
5383 llvm_unreachable("Target dependent opcode missing");
5384}
5385
5386bool ARMBaseInstrInfo::getInsertSubregLikeInputs(
5387 const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned DefIdx, RegSubRegPair &BaseReg,
5388 RegSubRegPairAndIdx &InsertedReg) const {
5389 assert(DefIdx < MI.getDesc().getNumDefs() && "Invalid definition index");
5390 assert(MI.isInsertSubregLike() && "Invalid kind of instruction");
5391
5392 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
5393 case ARM::VSETLNi32:
5394 // dX = VSETLNi32 dY, rZ, imm
5395 const MachineOperand &MOBaseReg = MI.getOperand(1);
5396 const MachineOperand &MOInsertedReg = MI.getOperand(2);
5397 if (MOInsertedReg.isUndef())
5398 return false;
5399 const MachineOperand &MOIndex = MI.getOperand(3);
5400 BaseReg.Reg = MOBaseReg.getReg();
5401 BaseReg.SubReg = MOBaseReg.getSubReg();
5402
5403 InsertedReg.Reg = MOInsertedReg.getReg();
5404 InsertedReg.SubReg = MOInsertedReg.getSubReg();
5405 InsertedReg.SubIdx = MOIndex.getImm() == 0 ? ARM::ssub_0 : ARM::ssub_1;
5406 return true;
5407 }
5408 llvm_unreachable("Target dependent opcode missing");
5409}

5439
5440Optional<RegImmPair> ARMBaseInstrInfo::isAddImmediate(const MachineInstr &MI,
5441 Register Reg) const {
5442 int Sign = 1;
5443 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode();
5444 int64_t Offset = 0;
5445
5446 // TODO: Handle cases where Reg is a super- or sub-register of the
5447 // destination register.
5448 const MachineOperand &Op0 = MI.getOperand(0);
5449 if (!Op0.isReg() || Reg != Op0.getReg())
5450 return None;
5451
5452 // We describe SUBri or ADDri instructions.
5453 if (Opcode == ARM::SUBri)
5454 Sign = -1;
5455 else if (Opcode != ARM::ADDri)
5456 return None;
5457
5458 // TODO: Third operand can be global address (usually some string). Since
5459 // strings can be relocated we cannot calculate their offsets for
5460 // now.
5461 if (!MI.getOperand(1).isReg() || !MI.getOperand(2).isImm())
5462 return None;
5463
5464 Offset = MI.getOperand(2).getImm() * Sign;
5465 return RegImmPair{MI.getOperand(1).getReg(), Offset};
5466}
5467
5468bool llvm::registerDefinedBetween(unsigned Reg,
5469 MachineBasicBlock::iterator From,
5470 MachineBasicBlock::iterator To,
5471 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) {
5472 for (auto I = From; I != To; ++I)
5473 if (I->modifiesRegister(Reg, TRI))
5474 return true;
5475 return false;
5476}
5477
5478MachineInstr *llvm::findCMPToFoldIntoCBZ(MachineInstr *Br,
5479 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) {
5480 // Search backwards to the instruction that defines CSPR. This may or not
5481 // be a CMP, we check that after this loop. If we find another instruction
5482 // that reads cpsr, we return nullptr.
5483 MachineBasicBlock::iterator CmpMI = Br;
5484 while (CmpMI != Br->getParent()->begin()) {
5485 --CmpMI;
5486 if (CmpMI->modifiesRegister(ARM::CPSR, TRI))
5487 break;
5488 if (CmpMI->readsRegister(ARM::CPSR, TRI))
5489 break;
5490 }
5491
5492 // Check that this inst is a CMP r[0-7], #0 and that the register
5493 // is not redefined between the cmp and the br.
5494 if (CmpMI->getOpcode() != ARM::tCMPi8 && CmpMI->getOpcode() != ARM::t2CMPri)
5495 return nullptr;
5496 Register Reg = CmpMI->getOperand(0).getReg();
5497 Register PredReg;
5498 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = getInstrPredicate(*CmpMI, PredReg);
5499 if (Pred != ARMCC::AL || CmpMI->getOperand(1).getImm() != 0)
5500 return nullptr;
5501 if (!isARMLowRegister(Reg))
5502 return nullptr;
5503 if (registerDefinedBetween(Reg, CmpMI->getNextNode(), Br, TRI))
5504 return nullptr;
5505
5506 return &*CmpMI;
5507}
5508
5509unsigned llvm::ConstantMaterializationCost(unsigned Val,
5510 const ARMSubtarget *Subtarget,
5511 bool ForCodesize) {
5512 if (Subtarget->isThumb()) {
5513 if (Val <= 255) // MOV
5514 return ForCodesize ? 2 : 1;
5515 if (Subtarget->hasV6T2Ops() && (Val <= 0xffff || // MOV
5516 ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(Val) != -1 || // MOVW
5517 ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(~Val) != -1)) // MVN
5518 return ForCodesize ? 4 : 1;
5519 if (Val <= 510) // MOV + ADDi8
5520 return ForCodesize ? 4 : 2;
5521 if (~Val <= 255) // MOV + MVN
5522 return ForCodesize ? 4 : 2;
5523 if (ARM_AM::isThumbImmShiftedVal(Val)) // MOV + LSL
5524 return ForCodesize ? 4 : 2;
5525 } else {
5526 if (ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(Val) != -1) // MOV
5527 return ForCodesize ? 4 : 1;
5528 if (ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(~Val) != -1) // MVN
5529 return ForCodesize ? 4 : 1;
5530 if (Subtarget->hasV6T2Ops() && Val <= 0xffff) // MOVW
5531 return ForCodesize ? 4 : 1;
5532 if (ARM_AM::isSOImmTwoPartVal(Val)) // two instrs
5533 return ForCodesize ? 8 : 2;
5534 if (ARM_AM::isSOImmTwoPartValNeg(Val)) // two instrs
5535 return ForCodesize ? 8 : 2;
5536 }
5537 if (Subtarget->useMovt()) // MOVW + MOVT
5538 return ForCodesize ? 8 : 2;
5539 return ForCodesize ? 8 : 3; // Literal pool load
5540}
5541
5542bool llvm::HasLowerConstantMaterializationCost(unsigned Val1, unsigned Val2,
5543 const ARMSubtarget *Subtarget,
5544 bool ForCodesize) {
5545 // Check with ForCodesize
5546 unsigned Cost1 = ConstantMaterializationCost(Val1, Subtarget, ForCodesize);
5547 unsigned Cost2 = ConstantMaterializationCost(Val2, Subtarget, ForCodesize);
5548 if (Cost1 < Cost2)
5549 return true;
5550 if (Cost1 > Cost2)
5551 return false;
5552
5553 // If they are equal, try with !ForCodesize
5554 return ConstantMaterializationCost(Val1, Subtarget, !ForCodesize) <
5555 ConstantMaterializationCost(Val2, Subtarget, !ForCodesize);
5556}
5557
5558/// Constants defining how certain sequences should be outlined.
5559/// This encompasses how an outlined function should be called, and what kind of
5560/// frame should be emitted for that outlined function.
5561///
5562/// \p MachineOutlinerTailCall implies that the function is being created from
5563/// a sequence of instructions ending in a return.
5564///
5565/// That is,
5566///
5567/// I1 OUTLINED_FUNCTION:
5568/// I2 --> B OUTLINED_FUNCTION I1
5569/// BX LR I2
5570/// BX LR
5571///
5572/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5573/// | | Thumb2 | ARM |
5574/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5575/// | Call overhead in Bytes | 4 | 4 |
5576/// | Frame overhead in Bytes | 0 | 0 |
5577/// | Stack fixup required | No | No |
5578/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5579///
5580/// \p MachineOutlinerThunk implies that the function is being created from
5581/// a sequence of instructions ending in a call. The outlined function is
5582/// called with a BL instruction, and the outlined function tail-calls the
5583/// original call destination.
5584///
5585/// That is,
5586///
5587/// I1 OUTLINED_FUNCTION:
5588/// I2 --> BL OUTLINED_FUNCTION I1
5589/// BL f I2
5590/// B f
5591///
5592/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5593/// | | Thumb2 | ARM |
5594/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5595/// | Call overhead in Bytes | 4 | 4 |
5596/// | Frame overhead in Bytes | 0 | 0 |
5597/// | Stack fixup required | No | No |
5598/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5599///
5600/// \p MachineOutlinerNoLRSave implies that the function should be called using
5601/// a BL instruction, but doesn't require LR to be saved and restored. This
5602/// happens when LR is known to be dead.
5603///
5604/// That is,
5605///
5606/// I1 OUTLINED_FUNCTION:
5607/// I2 --> BL OUTLINED_FUNCTION I1
5608/// I3 I2
5609/// I3
5610/// BX LR
5611///
5612/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5613/// | | Thumb2 | ARM |
5614/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5615/// | Call overhead in Bytes | 4 | 4 |
5616/// | Frame overhead in Bytes | 4 | 4 |
5617/// | Stack fixup required | No | No |
5618/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5619///
5620/// \p MachineOutlinerRegSave implies that the function should be called with a
5621/// save and restore of LR to an available register. This allows us to avoid
5622/// stack fixups. Note that this outlining variant is compatible with the
5623/// NoLRSave case.
5624///
5625/// That is,
5626///
5627/// I1 Save LR OUTLINED_FUNCTION:
5628/// I2 --> BL OUTLINED_FUNCTION I1
5629/// I3 Restore LR I2
5630/// I3
5631/// BX LR
5632///
5633/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5634/// | | Thumb2 | ARM |
5635/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5636/// | Call overhead in Bytes | 8 | 12 |
5637/// | Frame overhead in Bytes | 2 | 4 |
5638/// | Stack fixup required | No | No |
5639/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5640///
5641/// \p MachineOutlinerDefault implies that the function should be called with
5642/// a save and restore of LR to the stack.
5643///
5644/// That is,
5645///
5646/// I1 Save LR OUTLINED_FUNCTION:
5647/// I2 --> BL OUTLINED_FUNCTION I1
5648/// I3 Restore LR I2
5649/// I3
5650/// BX LR
5651///
5652/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5653/// | | Thumb2 | ARM |
5654/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5655/// | Call overhead in Bytes | 8 | 12 |
5656/// | Frame overhead in Bytes | 2 | 4 |
5657/// | Stack fixup required | Yes | Yes |
5658/// +-------------------------+--------+-----+
5659
5660enum MachineOutlinerClass {
5661 MachineOutlinerTailCall,
5662 MachineOutlinerThunk,
5663 MachineOutlinerNoLRSave,
5664 MachineOutlinerRegSave,
5665 MachineOutlinerDefault
5666};
5667
5668enum MachineOutlinerMBBFlags {
5669 LRUnavailableSomewhere = 0x2,
5670 HasCalls = 0x4,
5671 UnsafeRegsDead = 0x8
5672};
5673
5674struct OutlinerCosts {
5675 const int CallTailCall;
5676 const int FrameTailCall;
5677 const int CallThunk;
5678 const int FrameThunk;
5679 const int CallNoLRSave;
5680 const int FrameNoLRSave;
5681 const int CallRegSave;
5682 const int FrameRegSave;
5683 const int CallDefault;
5684 const int FrameDefault;
5685 const int SaveRestoreLROnStack;
5686
5687 OutlinerCosts(const ARMSubtarget &target)
5688 : CallTailCall(target.isThumb() ? 4 : 4),
5689 FrameTailCall(target.isThumb() ? 0 : 0),
5690 CallThunk(target.isThumb() ? 4 : 4),
5691 FrameThunk(target.isThumb() ? 0 : 0),
5692 CallNoLRSave(target.isThumb() ? 4 : 4),
5693 FrameNoLRSave(target.isThumb() ? 4 : 4),
5694 CallRegSave(target.isThumb() ? 8 : 12),
5695 FrameRegSave(target.isThumb() ? 2 : 4),
5696 CallDefault(target.isThumb() ? 8 : 12),
5697 FrameDefault(target.isThumb() ? 2 : 4),
5698 SaveRestoreLROnStack(target.isThumb() ? 8 : 8) {}
5699};
5700
5701unsigned
5702ARMBaseInstrInfo::findRegisterToSaveLRTo(const outliner::Candidate &C) const {
5703 assert(C.LRUWasSet && "LRU wasn't set?");
5704 MachineFunction *MF = C.getMF();
5705 const ARMBaseRegisterInfo *ARI = static_cast<const ARMBaseRegisterInfo *>(
5706 MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo());
5707
5708 BitVector regsReserved = ARI->getReservedRegs(*MF);
5709 // Check if there is an available register across the sequence that we can
5710 // use.
5711 for (unsigned Reg : ARM::rGPRRegClass) {
5712 if (!(Reg < regsReserved.size() && regsReserved.test(Reg)) &&
5713 Reg != ARM::LR && // LR is not reserved, but don't use it.
5714 Reg != ARM::R12 && // R12 is not guaranteed to be preserved.
5715 C.LRU.available(Reg) && C.UsedInSequence.available(Reg))
5716 return Reg;
5717 }
5718
5719 // No suitable register. Return 0.
5720 return 0u;
5721}
5722
5723// Compute liveness of LR at the point after the interval [I, E), which
5724// denotes a *backward* iteration through instructions. Used only for return
5725// basic blocks, which do not end with a tail call.
5726static bool isLRAvailable(const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI,
5727 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator I,
5728 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator E) {
5729 // At the end of the function LR dead.
5730 bool Live = false;
5731 for (; I != E; ++I) {
5732 const MachineInstr &MI = *I;
5733
5734 // Check defs of LR.
5735 if (MI.modifiesRegister(ARM::LR, &TRI))
5736 Live = false;
5737
5738 // Check uses of LR.
5739 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode();
5740 if (Opcode == ARM::BX_RET || Opcode == ARM::MOVPCLR ||
5741 Opcode == ARM::SUBS_PC_LR || Opcode == ARM::tBX_RET ||
5742 Opcode == ARM::tBXNS_RET) {
5743 // These instructions use LR, but it's not an (explicit or implicit)
5744 // operand.
5745 Live = true;
5746 continue;
5747 }
5748 if (MI.readsRegister(ARM::LR, &TRI))
5749 Live = true;
5750 }
5751 return !Live;
5752}
5753
5754outliner::OutlinedFunction ARMBaseInstrInfo::getOutliningCandidateInfo(
5755 std::vector<outliner::Candidate> &RepeatedSequenceLocs) const {
5756 outliner::Candidate &FirstCand = RepeatedSequenceLocs[0];
5757 unsigned SequenceSize =
5758 std::accumulate(FirstCand.front(), std::next(FirstCand.back()), 0,
5759 [this](unsigned Sum, const MachineInstr &MI) {
5760 return Sum + getInstSizeInBytes(MI);
5761 });
5762
5763 // Properties about candidate MBBs that hold for all of them.
5764 unsigned FlagsSetInAll = 0xF;
5765
5766 // Compute liveness information for each candidate, and set FlagsSetInAll.
5767 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI = getRegisterInfo();
5768 std::for_each(
5769 RepeatedSequenceLocs.begin(), RepeatedSequenceLocs.end(),
5770 [&FlagsSetInAll](outliner::Candidate &C) { FlagsSetInAll &= C.Flags; });
5771
5772 // According to the ARM Procedure Call Standard, the following are
5773 // undefined on entry/exit from a function call:
5774 //
5775 // * Register R12(IP),
5776 // * Condition codes (and thus the CPSR register)
5777 //
5778 // Since we control the instructions which are part of the outlined regions
5779 // we don't need to be fully compliant with the AAPCS, but we have to
5780 // guarantee that if a veneer is inserted at link time the code is still
5781 // correct. Because of this, we can't outline any sequence of instructions
5782 // where one of these registers is live into/across it. Thus, we need to
5783 // delete those candidates.
5784 auto CantGuaranteeValueAcrossCall = [&TRI](outliner::Candidate &C) {
5785 // If the unsafe registers in this block are all dead, then we don't need
5786 // to compute liveness here.
5787 if (C.Flags & UnsafeRegsDead)
5788 return false;
5789 C.initLRU(TRI);
5790 LiveRegUnits LRU = C.LRU;
5791 return (!LRU.available(ARM::R12) || !LRU.available(ARM::CPSR));
5792 };
5793
5794 // Are there any candidates where those registers are live?
5795 if (!(FlagsSetInAll & UnsafeRegsDead)) {
5796 // Erase every candidate that violates the restrictions above. (It could be
5797 // true that we have viable candidates, so it's not worth bailing out in
5798 // the case that, say, 1 out of 20 candidates violate the restructions.)
5799 llvm::erase_if(RepeatedSequenceLocs, CantGuaranteeValueAcrossCall);
5800
5801 // If the sequence doesn't have enough candidates left, then we're done.
5802 if (RepeatedSequenceLocs.size() < 2)
5803 return outliner::OutlinedFunction();
5804 }
5805
5806 // At this point, we have only "safe" candidates to outline. Figure out
5807 // frame + call instruction information.
5808
5809 unsigned LastInstrOpcode = RepeatedSequenceLocs[0].back()->getOpcode();
5810
5811 // Helper lambda which sets call information for every candidate.
5812 auto SetCandidateCallInfo =
5813 [&RepeatedSequenceLocs](unsigned CallID, unsigned NumBytesForCall) {
5814 for (outliner::Candidate &C : RepeatedSequenceLocs)
5815 C.setCallInfo(CallID, NumBytesForCall);
5816 };
5817
5818 OutlinerCosts Costs(Subtarget);
5819 unsigned FrameID = MachineOutlinerDefault;
5820 unsigned NumBytesToCreateFrame = Costs.FrameDefault;
5821
5822 // If the last instruction in any candidate is a terminator, then we should
5823 // tail call all of the candidates.
5824 if (RepeatedSequenceLocs[0].back()->isTerminator()) {
5825 FrameID = MachineOutlinerTailCall;
5826 NumBytesToCreateFrame = Costs.FrameTailCall;
5827 SetCandidateCallInfo(MachineOutlinerTailCall, Costs.CallTailCall);
5828 } else if (LastInstrOpcode == ARM::BL || LastInstrOpcode == ARM::BLX ||
5829 LastInstrOpcode == ARM::BLX_noip || LastInstrOpcode == ARM::tBL ||
5830 LastInstrOpcode == ARM::tBLXr ||
5831 LastInstrOpcode == ARM::tBLXr_noip ||
5832 LastInstrOpcode == ARM::tBLXi) {
5833 FrameID = MachineOutlinerThunk;
5834 NumBytesToCreateFrame = Costs.FrameThunk;
5835 SetCandidateCallInfo(MachineOutlinerThunk, Costs.CallThunk);
5836 } else {
5837 // We need to decide how to emit calls + frames. We can always emit the same
5838 // frame if we don't need to save to the stack. If we have to save to the
5839 // stack, then we need a different frame.
5840 unsigned NumBytesNoStackCalls = 0;
5841 std::vector<outliner::Candidate> CandidatesWithoutStackFixups;
5842
5843 for (outliner::Candidate &C : RepeatedSequenceLocs) {
5844 C.initLRU(TRI);
5845 // LR liveness is overestimated in return blocks, unless they end with a
5846 // tail call.
5847 const auto Last = C.getMBB()->rbegin();
5848 const bool LRIsAvailable =
5849 C.getMBB()->isReturnBlock() && !Last->isCall()
5850 ? isLRAvailable(TRI, Last,
5851 (MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator)C.front())
5852 : C.LRU.available(ARM::LR);
5853 if (LRIsAvailable) {
5854 FrameID = MachineOutlinerNoLRSave;
5855 NumBytesNoStackCalls += Costs.CallNoLRSave;
5856 C.setCallInfo(MachineOutlinerNoLRSave, Costs.CallNoLRSave);
5857 CandidatesWithoutStackFixups.push_back(C);
5858 }
5859
5860 // Is an unused register available? If so, we won't modify the stack, so
5861 // we can outline with the same frame type as those that don't save LR.
5862 else if (findRegisterToSaveLRTo(C)) {
5863 FrameID = MachineOutlinerRegSave;
5864 NumBytesNoStackCalls += Costs.CallRegSave;
5865 C.setCallInfo(MachineOutlinerRegSave, Costs.CallRegSave);
5866 CandidatesWithoutStackFixups.push_back(C);
5867 }
5868
5869 // Is SP used in the sequence at all? If not, we don't have to modify
5870 // the stack, so we are guaranteed to get the same frame.
5871 else if (C.UsedInSequence.available(ARM::SP)) {
5872 NumBytesNoStackCalls += Costs.CallDefault;
5873 C.setCallInfo(MachineOutlinerDefault, Costs.CallDefault);
5874 CandidatesWithoutStackFixups.push_back(C);
5875 }
5876
5877 // If we outline this, we need to modify the stack. Pretend we don't
5878 // outline this by saving all of its bytes.
5879 else
5880 NumBytesNoStackCalls += SequenceSize;
5881 }
5882
5883 // If there are no places where we have to save LR, then note that we don't
5884 // have to update the stack. Otherwise, give every candidate the default
5885 // call type
5886 if (NumBytesNoStackCalls <=
5887 RepeatedSequenceLocs.size() * Costs.CallDefault) {
5888 RepeatedSequenceLocs = CandidatesWithoutStackFixups;
5889 FrameID = MachineOutlinerNoLRSave;
5890 } else
5891 SetCandidateCallInfo(MachineOutlinerDefault, Costs.CallDefault);
5892 }
5893
5894 // Does every candidate's MBB contain a call? If so, then we might have a
5895 // call in the range.
5896 if (FlagsSetInAll & MachineOutlinerMBBFlags::HasCalls) {
5897 // check if the range contains a call. These require a save + restore of
5898 // the link register.
5899 if (std::any_of(FirstCand.front(), FirstCand.back(),
5900 [](const MachineInstr &MI) { return MI.isCall(); }))
5901 NumBytesToCreateFrame += Costs.SaveRestoreLROnStack;
5902
5903 // Handle the last instruction separately. If it is tail call, then the
5904 // last instruction is a call, we don't want to save + restore in this
5905 // case. However, it could be possible that the last instruction is a
5906 // call without it being valid to tail call this sequence. We should
5907 // consider this as well.
5908 else if (FrameID != MachineOutlinerThunk &&
5909 FrameID != MachineOutlinerTailCall && FirstCand.back()->isCall())
5910 NumBytesToCreateFrame += Costs.SaveRestoreLROnStack;
5911 }
5912
5913 return outliner::OutlinedFunction(RepeatedSequenceLocs, SequenceSize,
5914 NumBytesToCreateFrame, FrameID);
5915}
5916
5917bool ARMBaseInstrInfo::checkAndUpdateStackOffset(MachineInstr *MI,
5918 int64_t Fixup,
5919 bool Updt) const {
5920 int SPIdx = MI->findRegisterUseOperandIdx(ARM::SP);
5921 unsigned AddrMode = (MI->getDesc().TSFlags & ARMII::AddrModeMask);
5922 if (SPIdx < 0)
5923 // No SP operand
5924 return true;
5925 else if (SPIdx != 1 && (AddrMode != ARMII::AddrModeT2_i8s4 || SPIdx != 2))
5926 // If SP is not the base register we can't do much
5927 return false;
5928
5929 // Stack might be involved but addressing mode doesn't handle any offset.
5930 // Rq: AddrModeT1_[1|2|4] don't operate on SP
5931 if (AddrMode == ARMII::AddrMode1 // Arithmetic instructions
5932 || AddrMode == ARMII::AddrMode4 // Load/Store Multiple
5933 || AddrMode == ARMII::AddrMode6 // Neon Load/Store Multiple
5934 || AddrMode == ARMII::AddrModeT2_so // SP can't be used as based register
5935 || AddrMode == ARMII::AddrModeT2_pc // PCrel access
5936 || AddrMode == ARMII::AddrMode2 // Used by PRE and POST indexed LD/ST
5937 || AddrMode == ARMII::AddrModeNone)
5938 return false;
5939
5940 unsigned NumOps = MI->getDesc().getNumOperands();
5941 unsigned ImmIdx = NumOps - 3;
5942
5943 const MachineOperand &Offset = MI->getOperand(ImmIdx);
5944 assert(Offset.isImm() && "Is not an immediate");
5945 int64_t OffVal = Offset.getImm();
5946
5947 if (OffVal < 0)
5948 // Don't override data if the are below SP.
5949 return false;
5950
5951 unsigned NumBits = 0;
5952 unsigned Scale = 1;
5953
5954 switch (AddrMode) {
5955 case ARMII::AddrMode3:
5956 if (ARM_AM::getAM3Op(OffVal) == ARM_AM::sub)
5957 return false;
5958 OffVal = ARM_AM::getAM3Offset(OffVal);
5959 NumBits = 8;
5960 break;
5961 case ARMII::AddrMode5:
5962 if (ARM_AM::getAM5Op(OffVal) == ARM_AM::sub)
5963 return false;
5964 OffVal = ARM_AM::getAM5Offset(OffVal);
5965 NumBits = 8;
5966 Scale = 4;
5967 break;
5968 case ARMII::AddrMode5FP16:
5969 if (ARM_AM::getAM5FP16Op(OffVal) == ARM_AM::sub)
5970 return false;
5971 OffVal = ARM_AM::getAM5FP16Offset(OffVal);
5972 NumBits = 8;
5973 Scale = 2;
5974 break;
5975 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i8:
5976 NumBits = 8;
5977 break;
5978 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i8s4:
5979 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_ldrex:
5980 NumBits = 8;
5981 Scale = 4;
5982 break;
5983 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i12:
5984 case ARMII::AddrMode_i12:
5985 NumBits = 12;
5986 break;
5987 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i7:
5988 NumBits = 7;
5989 break;
5990 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i7s2:
5991 NumBits = 7;
5992 Scale = 2;
5993 break;
5994 case ARMII::AddrModeT2_i7s4:
5995 NumBits = 7;
5996 Scale = 4;
5997 break;
5998 case ARMII::AddrModeT1_s: // SP-relative LD/ST
5999 NumBits = 8;
6000 Scale = 4;
6001 break;
6002 default:
6003 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported addressing mode!");
6004 }
6005 // Make sure the offset is encodable for instructions that scale the
6006 // immediate.
6007 if (((OffVal * Scale + Fixup) & (Scale - 1)) != 0)
6008 return false;
6009 OffVal += Fixup / Scale;
6010
6011 unsigned Mask = (1 << NumBits) - 1;
6012
6013 if (OffVal <= Mask) {
6014 if (Updt)
6015 MI->getOperand(ImmIdx).setImm(OffVal);
6016 return true;
6017 }
6018
6019 return false;
6020
6021}
6022
6023bool ARMBaseInstrInfo::isFunctionSafeToOutlineFrom(
6024 MachineFunction &MF, bool OutlineFromLinkOnceODRs) const {
6025 const Function &F = MF.getFunction();
6026
6027 // Can F be deduplicated by the linker? If it can, don't outline from it.
6028 if (!OutlineFromLinkOnceODRs && F.hasLinkOnceODRLinkage())
6029 return false;
6030
6031 // Don't outline from functions with section markings; the program could
6032 // expect that all the code is in the named section.
6033 // FIXME: Allow outlining from multiple functions with the same section
6034 // marking.
6035 if (F.hasSection())
6036 return false;
6037
6038 // FIXME: Thumb1 outlining is not handled
6039 if (MF.getInfo<ARMFunctionInfo>()->isThumb1OnlyFunction())
6040 return false;
6041
6042 // It's safe to outline from MF.
6043 return true;
6044}
6045
6046bool ARMBaseInstrInfo::isMBBSafeToOutlineFrom(MachineBasicBlock &MBB,
6047 unsigned &Flags) const {
6048 // Check if LR is available through all of the MBB. If it's not, then set
6049 // a flag.
6050 assert(MBB.getParent()->getRegInfo().tracksLiveness() &&
6051 "Suitable Machine Function for outlining must track liveness");
6052
6053 LiveRegUnits LRU(getRegisterInfo());
6054
6055 std::for_each(MBB.rbegin(), MBB.rend(),
6056 [&LRU](MachineInstr &MI) { LRU.accumulate(MI); });
6057
6058 // Check if each of the unsafe registers are available...
6059 bool R12AvailableInBlock = LRU.available(ARM::R12);
6060 bool CPSRAvailableInBlock = LRU.available(ARM::CPSR);
6061
6062 // If all of these are dead (and not live out), we know we don't have to check
6063 // them later.
6064 if (R12AvailableInBlock && CPSRAvailableInBlock)
6065 Flags |= MachineOutlinerMBBFlags::UnsafeRegsDead;
6066
6067 // Now, add the live outs to the set.
6068 LRU.addLiveOuts(MBB);
6069
6070 // If any of these registers is available in the MBB, but also a live out of
6071 // the block, then we know outlining is unsafe.
6072 if (R12AvailableInBlock && !LRU.available(ARM::R12))
6073 return false;
6074 if (CPSRAvailableInBlock && !LRU.available(ARM::CPSR))
6075 return false;
6076
6077 // Check if there's a call inside this MachineBasicBlock. If there is, then
6078 // set a flag.
6079 if (any_of(MBB, [](MachineInstr &MI) { return MI.isCall(); }))
6080 Flags |= MachineOutlinerMBBFlags::HasCalls;
6081
6082 // LR liveness is overestimated in return blocks.
6083
6084 bool LRIsAvailable =
6085 MBB.isReturnBlock() && !MBB.back().isCall()
6086 ? isLRAvailable(getRegisterInfo(), MBB.rbegin(), MBB.rend())
6087 : LRU.available(ARM::LR);
6088 if (!LRIsAvailable)
6089 Flags |= MachineOutlinerMBBFlags::LRUnavailableSomewhere;
6090
6091 return true;
6092}
6093
6094outliner::InstrType
6095ARMBaseInstrInfo::getOutliningType(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MIT,
6096 unsigned Flags) const {
6097 MachineInstr &MI = *MIT;
6098 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = &getRegisterInfo();
6099
6100 // Be conservative with inline ASM
6101 if (MI.isInlineAsm())
6102 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6103
6104 // Don't allow debug values to impact outlining type.
6105 if (MI.isDebugInstr() || MI.isIndirectDebugValue())
6106 return outliner::InstrType::Invisible;
6107
6108 // At this point, KILL or IMPLICIT_DEF instructions don't really tell us much
6109 // so we can go ahead and skip over them.
6110 if (MI.isKill() || MI.isImplicitDef())
6111 return outliner::InstrType::Invisible;
6112
6113 // PIC instructions contain labels, outlining them would break offset
6114 // computing. unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
6115 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
6116 if (Opc == ARM::tPICADD || Opc == ARM::PICADD || Opc == ARM::PICSTR ||
6117 Opc == ARM::PICSTRB || Opc == ARM::PICSTRH || Opc == ARM::PICLDR ||
6118 Opc == ARM::PICLDRB || Opc == ARM::PICLDRH || Opc == ARM::PICLDRSB ||
6119 Opc == ARM::PICLDRSH || Opc == ARM::t2LDRpci_pic ||
6120 Opc == ARM::t2MOVi16_ga_pcrel || Opc == ARM::t2MOVTi16_ga_pcrel ||
6121 Opc == ARM::t2MOV_ga_pcrel)
6122 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6123
6124 // Be conservative with ARMv8.1 MVE instructions.
6125 if (Opc == ARM::t2BF_LabelPseudo || Opc == ARM::t2DoLoopStart ||
6126 Opc == ARM::t2DoLoopStartTP || Opc == ARM::t2WhileLoopStart ||
6127 Opc == ARM::t2LoopDec || Opc == ARM::t2LoopEnd ||
6128 Opc == ARM::t2LoopEndDec)
6129 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6130
6131 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI.getDesc();
6132 uint64_t MIFlags = MCID.TSFlags;
6133 if ((MIFlags & ARMII::DomainMask) == ARMII::DomainMVE)
6134 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6135
6136 // Is this a terminator for a basic block?
6137 if (MI.isTerminator()) {
6138 // Don't outline if the branch is not unconditional.
6139 if (isPredicated(MI))
6140 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6141
6142 // Is this the end of a function?
6143 if (MI.getParent()->succ_empty())
6144 return outliner::InstrType::Legal;
6145
6146 // It's not, so don't outline it.
6147 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6148 }
6149
6150 // Make sure none of the operands are un-outlinable.
6151 for (const MachineOperand &MOP : MI.operands()) {
6152 if (MOP.isCPI() || MOP.isJTI() || MOP.isCFIIndex() || MOP.isFI() ||
6153 MOP.isTargetIndex())
6154 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6155 }
6156
6157 // Don't outline if link register or program counter value are used.
6158 if (MI.readsRegister(ARM::LR, TRI) || MI.readsRegister(ARM::PC, TRI))
6159 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6160
6161 if (MI.isCall()) {
6162 // Get the function associated with the call. Look at each operand and find
6163 // the one that represents the calle and get its name.
6164 const Function *Callee = nullptr;
6165 for (const MachineOperand &MOP : MI.operands()) {
6166 if (MOP.isGlobal()) {
6167 Callee = dyn_cast<Function>(MOP.getGlobal());
6168 break;
6169 }
6170 }
6171
6172 // Dont't outline calls to "mcount" like functions, in particular Linux
6173 // kernel function tracing relies on it.
6174 if (Callee &&
6175 (Callee->getName() == "\01__gnu_mcount_nc" ||
6176 Callee->getName() == "\01mcount" || Callee->getName() == "__mcount"))
6177 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6178
6179 // If we don't know anything about the callee, assume it depends on the
6180 // stack layout of the caller. In that case, it's only legal to outline
6181 // as a tail-call. Explicitly list the call instructions we know about so
6182 // we don't get unexpected results with call pseudo-instructions.
6183 auto UnknownCallOutlineType = outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6184 if (Opc == ARM::BL || Opc == ARM::tBL || Opc == ARM::BLX ||
6185 Opc == ARM::BLX_noip || Opc == ARM::tBLXr || Opc == ARM::tBLXr_noip ||
6186 Opc == ARM::tBLXi)
6187 UnknownCallOutlineType = outliner::InstrType::LegalTerminator;
6188
6189 if (!Callee)
6190 return UnknownCallOutlineType;
6191
6192 // We have a function we have information about. Check if it's something we
6193 // can safely outline.
6194 MachineFunction *MF = MI.getParent()->getParent();
6195 MachineFunction *CalleeMF = MF->getMMI().getMachineFunction(*Callee);
6196
6197 // We don't know what's going on with the callee at all. Don't touch it.
6198 if (!CalleeMF)
6199 return UnknownCallOutlineType;
6200
6201 // Check if we know anything about the callee saves on the function. If we
6202 // don't, then don't touch it, since that implies that we haven't computed
6203 // anything about its stack frame yet.
6204 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = CalleeMF->getFrameInfo();
6205 if (!MFI.isCalleeSavedInfoValid() || MFI.getStackSize() > 0 ||
6206 MFI.getNumObjects() > 0)
6207 return UnknownCallOutlineType;
6208
6209 // At this point, we can say that CalleeMF ought to not pass anything on the
6210 // stack. Therefore, we can outline it.
6211 return outliner::InstrType::Legal;
6212 }
6213
6214 // Since calls are handled, don't touch LR or PC
6215 if (MI.modifiesRegister(ARM::LR, TRI) || MI.modifiesRegister(ARM::PC, TRI))
6216 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6217
6218 // Does this use the stack?
6219 if (MI.modifiesRegister(ARM::SP, TRI) || MI.readsRegister(ARM::SP, TRI)) {
6220 // True if there is no chance that any outlined candidate from this range
6221 // could require stack fixups. That is, both
6222 // * LR is available in the range (No save/restore around call)
6223 // * The range doesn't include calls (No save/restore in outlined frame)
6224 // are true.
6225 // FIXME: This is very restrictive; the flags check the whole block,
6226 // not just the bit we will try to outline.
6227 bool MightNeedStackFixUp =
6228 (Flags & (MachineOutlinerMBBFlags::LRUnavailableSomewhere |
6229 MachineOutlinerMBBFlags::HasCalls));
6230
6231 if (!MightNeedStackFixUp)
6232 return outliner::InstrType::Legal;
6233
6234 // Any modification of SP will break our code to save/restore LR.
6235 // FIXME: We could handle some instructions which add a constant offset to
6236 // SP, with a bit more work.
6237 if (MI.modifiesRegister(ARM::SP, TRI))
6238 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6239
6240 // At this point, we have a stack instruction that we might need to fix up.
6241 // up. We'll handle it if it's a load or store.
6242 if (checkAndUpdateStackOffset(&MI, Subtarget.getStackAlignment().value(),
6243 false))
6244 return outliner::InstrType::Legal;
6245
6246 // We can't fix it up, so don't outline it.
6247 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6248 }
6249
6250 // Be conservative with IT blocks.
6251 if (MI.readsRegister(ARM::ITSTATE, TRI) ||
6252 MI.modifiesRegister(ARM::ITSTATE, TRI))
6253 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6254
6255 // Don't outline positions.
6256 if (MI.isPosition())
6257 return outliner::InstrType::Illegal;
6258
6259 return outliner::InstrType::Legal;
6260}
6261
6262void ARMBaseInstrInfo::fixupPostOutline(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) const {
6263 for (MachineInstr &MI : MBB) {
6264 checkAndUpdateStackOffset(&MI, Subtarget.getStackAlignment().value(), true);
6265 }
6266}

6268void ARMBaseInstrInfo::saveLROnStack(MachineBasicBlock &MBB,
6269 MachineBasicBlock::iterator It) const {
6270 unsigned Opc = Subtarget.isThumb() ? ARM::t2STR_PRE : ARM::STR_PRE_IMM;
6271 int Align = -Subtarget.getStackAlignment().value();
6272 BuildMI(MBB, It, DebugLoc(), get(Opc), ARM::SP)
6273 .addReg(ARM::LR, RegState::Kill)
6274 .addReg(ARM::SP)
6275 .addImm(Align)
6276 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
6277}
6278
6279void ARMBaseInstrInfo::emitCFIForLRSaveOnStack(
6280 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator It) const {
6281 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB.getParent();
6282 const MCRegisterInfo *MRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
6283 unsigned DwarfLR = MRI->getDwarfRegNum(ARM::LR, true);
6284 int Align = Subtarget.getStackAlignment().value();
6285 // Add a CFI saying the stack was moved down.
6286 int64_t StackPosEntry =
6287 MF.addFrameInst(MCCFIInstruction::cfiDefCfaOffset(nullptr, Align));
6288 BuildMI(MBB, It, DebugLoc(), get(ARM::CFI_INSTRUCTION))
6289 .addCFIIndex(StackPosEntry)
6290 .setMIFlags(MachineInstr::FrameSetup);
6291
6292 // Add a CFI saying that the LR that we want to find is now higher than
6293 // before.
6294 int64_t LRPosEntry =
6295 MF.addFrameInst(MCCFIInstruction::createOffset(nullptr, DwarfLR, -Align));
6296 BuildMI(MBB, It, DebugLoc(), get(ARM::CFI_INSTRUCTION))
6297 .addCFIIndex(LRPosEntry)
6298 .setMIFlags(MachineInstr::FrameSetup);
6299}

6303 Register Reg) const {

6305 const MCRegisterInfo *MRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
6306 unsigned DwarfLR = MRI->getDwarfRegNum(ARM::LR, true);
6307 unsigned DwarfReg = MRI->getDwarfRegNum(Reg, true);
6308
6309 int64_t LRPosEntry = MF.addFrameInst(
6310 MCCFIInstruction::createRegister(nullptr, DwarfLR, DwarfReg));
6311 BuildMI(MBB, It, DebugLoc(), get(ARM::CFI_INSTRUCTION))
6312 .addCFIIndex(LRPosEntry)
6313 .setMIFlags(MachineInstr::FrameSetup);
6314}

6316void ARMBaseInstrInfo::restoreLRFromStack(
6317 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator It) const {
6318 unsigned Opc = Subtarget.isThumb() ? ARM::t2LDR_POST : ARM::LDR_POST_IMM;
6319 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, It, DebugLoc(), get(Opc), ARM::LR)
6320 .addReg(ARM::SP, RegState::Define)
6321 .addReg(ARM::SP);
6322 if (!Subtarget.isThumb())
6323 MIB.addReg(0);
6324 MIB.addImm(Subtarget.getStackAlignment().value()).add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
6325}
6326
6327void ARMBaseInstrInfo::emitCFIForLRRestoreFromStack(
6328 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator It) const {
6329 // Now stack has moved back up...
6330 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB.getParent();
6331 const MCRegisterInfo *MRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
6332 unsigned DwarfLR = MRI->getDwarfRegNum(ARM::LR, true);
6333 int64_t StackPosEntry =
6334 MF.addFrameInst(MCCFIInstruction::cfiDefCfaOffset(nullptr, 0));
6335 BuildMI(MBB, It, DebugLoc(), get(ARM::CFI_INSTRUCTION))
6336 .addCFIIndex(StackPosEntry)
6337 .setMIFlags(MachineInstr::FrameDestroy);
6338
6339 // ... and we have restored LR.
6340 int64_t LRPosEntry =
6341 MF.addFrameInst(MCCFIInstruction::createRestore(nullptr, DwarfLR));
6342 BuildMI(MBB, It, DebugLoc(), get(ARM::CFI_INSTRUCTION))
6343 .addCFIIndex(LRPosEntry)
6344 .setMIFlags(MachineInstr::FrameDestroy);
6345}

6351 unsigned DwarfLR = MRI->getDwarfRegNum(ARM::LR, true);
6352

6354 MF.addFrameInst(MCCFIInstruction::createRestore(nullptr, DwarfLR));

6359
6360void ARMBaseInstrInfo::buildOutlinedFrame(
6361 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineFunction &MF,
6362 const outliner::OutlinedFunction &OF) const {
6363 // For thunk outlining, rewrite the last instruction from a call to a
6364 // tail-call.
6365 if (OF.FrameConstructionID == MachineOutlinerThunk) {
6366 MachineInstr *Call = &*--MBB.instr_end();
6367 bool isThumb = Subtarget.isThumb();
6368 unsigned FuncOp = isThumb ? 2 : 0;
6369 unsigned Opc = Call->getOperand(FuncOp).isReg()
6370 ? isThumb ? ARM::tTAILJMPr : ARM::TAILJMPr
6371 : isThumb ? Subtarget.isTargetMachO() ? ARM::tTAILJMPd
6372 : ARM::tTAILJMPdND
6373 : ARM::TAILJMPd;
6374 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, MBB.end(), DebugLoc(), get(Opc))
6375 .add(Call->getOperand(FuncOp));
6376 if (isThumb && !Call->getOperand(FuncOp).isReg())
6377 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
6378 Call->eraseFromParent();
6379 }
6380
6381 // Is there a call in the outlined range?
6382 auto IsNonTailCall = [](MachineInstr &MI) {
6383 return MI.isCall() && !MI.isReturn();
6384 };
6385 if (llvm::any_of(MBB.instrs(), IsNonTailCall)) {
6386 MachineBasicBlock::iterator It = MBB.begin();
6387 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Et = MBB.end();
6388
6389 if (OF.FrameConstructionID == MachineOutlinerTailCall ||
6390 OF.FrameConstructionID == MachineOutlinerThunk)
6391 Et = std::prev(MBB.end());
6392
6393 // We have to save and restore LR, we need to add it to the liveins if it
6394 // is not already part of the set. This is suffient since outlined
6395 // functions only have one block.
6396 if (!MBB.isLiveIn(ARM::LR))
6397 MBB.addLiveIn(ARM::LR);
6398
6399 // Insert a save before the outlined region
6400 saveLROnStack(MBB, It);
6401 emitCFIForLRSaveOnStack(MBB, It);
6402
6403 // Fix up the instructions in the range, since we're going to modify the
6404 // stack.
6405 assert(OF.FrameConstructionID != MachineOutlinerDefault &&
6406 "Can only fix up stack references once");
6407 fixupPostOutline(MBB);
6408
6409 // Insert a restore before the terminator for the function. Restore LR.
6410 restoreLRFromStack(MBB, Et);
6411 emitCFIForLRRestoreFromStack(MBB, Et);
6412 }
6413
6414 // If this is a tail call outlined function, then there's already a return.
6415 if (OF.FrameConstructionID == MachineOutlinerTailCall ||
6416 OF.FrameConstructionID == MachineOutlinerThunk)
6417 return;
6418
6419 // Here we have to insert the return ourselves. Get the correct opcode from
6420 // current feature set.
6421 BuildMI(MBB, MBB.end(), DebugLoc(), get(Subtarget.getReturnOpcode()))
6422 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
6423
6424 // Did we have to modify the stack by saving the link register?
6425 if (OF.FrameConstructionID != MachineOutlinerDefault &&
6426 OF.Candidates[0].CallConstructionID != MachineOutlinerDefault)
6427 return;
6428
6429 // We modified the stack.
6430 // Walk over the basic block and fix up all the stack accesses.
6431 fixupPostOutline(MBB);
6432}
6433
6434MachineBasicBlock::iterator ARMBaseInstrInfo::insertOutlinedCall(
6435 Module &M, MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator &It,
6436 MachineFunction &MF, const outliner::Candidate &C) const {
6437 MachineInstrBuilder MIB;
6438 MachineBasicBlock::iterator CallPt;
6439 unsigned Opc;
6440 bool isThumb = Subtarget.isThumb();
6441
6442 // Are we tail calling?
6443 if (C.CallConstructionID == MachineOutlinerTailCall) {
6444 // If yes, then we can just branch to the label.
6445 Opc = isThumb
6446 ? Subtarget.isTargetMachO() ? ARM::tTAILJMPd : ARM::tTAILJMPdND
6447 : ARM::TAILJMPd;
6448 MIB = BuildMI(MF, DebugLoc(), get(Opc))
6449 .addGlobalAddress(M.getNamedValue(MF.getName()));
6450 if (isThumb)
6451 MIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
6452 It = MBB.insert(It, MIB);
6453 return It;
6454 }
6455
6456 // Create the call instruction.
6457 Opc = isThumb ? ARM::tBL : ARM::BL;
6458 MachineInstrBuilder CallMIB = BuildMI(MF, DebugLoc(), get(Opc));
6459 if (isThumb)
6460 CallMIB.add(predOps(ARMCC::AL));
6461 CallMIB.addGlobalAddress(M.getNamedValue(MF.getName()));
6462
6463 if (C.CallConstructionID == MachineOutlinerNoLRSave ||
6464 C.CallConstructionID == MachineOutlinerThunk) {
6465 // No, so just insert the call.
6466 It = MBB.insert(It, CallMIB);
6467 return It;
6468 }
6469
6470 const ARMFunctionInfo &AFI = *C.getMF()->getInfo<ARMFunctionInfo>();
6471 // Can we save to a register?
6472 if (C.CallConstructionID == MachineOutlinerRegSave) {
6473 unsigned Reg = findRegisterToSaveLRTo(C);
6474 assert(Reg != 0 && "No callee-saved register available?");
6475
6476 // Save and restore LR from that register.
6477 copyPhysReg(MBB, It, DebugLoc(), Reg, ARM::LR, true);
6478 if (!AFI.isLRSpilled())
6479 emitCFIForLRSaveToReg(MBB, It, Reg);
6480 CallPt = MBB.insert(It, CallMIB);
6481 copyPhysReg(MBB, It, DebugLoc(), ARM::LR, Reg, true);
6482 if (!AFI.isLRSpilled())
6483 emitCFIForLRRestoreFromReg(MBB, It);
6484 It--;
6485 return CallPt;
6486 }
6487 // We have the default case. Save and restore from SP.
6488 if (!MBB.isLiveIn(ARM::LR))
6489 MBB.addLiveIn(ARM::LR);
6490 saveLROnStack(MBB, It);
6491 if (!AFI.isLRSpilled())
6492 emitCFIForLRSaveOnStack(MBB, It);
6493 CallPt = MBB.insert(It, CallMIB);
6494 restoreLRFromStack(MBB, It);
6495 if (!AFI.isLRSpilled())
6496 emitCFIForLRRestoreFromStack(MBB, It);
6497 It--;
6498 return CallPt;
6499}
6500
6501bool ARMBaseInstrInfo::shouldOutlineFromFunctionByDefault(
6502 MachineFunction &MF) const {
6503 return Subtarget.isMClass() && MF.getFunction().hasMinSize();
6504}
6505
6506bool ARMBaseInstrInfo::isReallyTriviallyReMaterializable(const MachineInstr &MI,
6507 AAResults *AA) const {
6508 // Try hard to rematerialize any VCTPs because if we spill P0, it will block
6509 // the tail predication conversion. This means that the element count
6510 // register has to be live for longer, but that has to be better than
6511 // spill/restore and VPT predication.
6512 return isVCTP(&MI) && !isPredicated(MI);
6513}
